- Install xautomation[1].
- Edit the script xplane.sh to match your joystick.
- make
- Install to wherever you like (and adjust the paths in xplane.sh appropriately).
- Enjoy!

Austin has stated that he is not interested in implementing a
fix, though he has admitted it would not be difficult. If you find this
useful, please drop a note to austin@xplane.com and linux@xplane.com and let
them know you would appreciate it if they would consider fixing X-Plane itself. 

1. http://hoopajoo.net/projects/xautomation.html
